Subject: [PATCH] default to 25000 variants per region

This provides the best performance on a 48-core machine, and for small graphs,
less than this size, we don't get much benefit out of multithreading. The
overheads of the reduce part of the process nullify the improvement.
---
 main.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/main.cpp b/main.cpp
index 66cef548f45..1d5447b22ff 100644
--- a/main.cpp
+++ b/main.cpp
@@ -1091,7 +1091,7 @@ int main_construct(int argc, char** argv) {
     string region;
     string output_type = "VG";
     bool progress = false;
-    int vars_per_region = 10000;
+    int vars_per_region = 25000;
 
     int c;
     while (true) {
